Kazakhstan competed at the 2014 FEI World Equestrian Games in the region of Normandy, France. Kazakhstan was represented by seven athletes competing in the dressage and endurance events.

== Dressage ==
Kazakhstan has qualified one team of three riders in dressage. Yurkevich was forced to withdrew after her horse Donpetro failed to pass the vet check day before the competition.

== Endurance ==
Kazakhstan has qualified one team of five athletes in endurance.

